<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1545,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[361,508,1545,1570]" captionStart="FIGURES 97 – 102" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1941,1964]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,445,1920]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 97 – 102. Holopypes habitus, dorsal view (up) and lateral view (down). 97, P. (F.) bahiensis sp. nov. 98, P. (F.) grossii sp. nov. 99, P. (F.) intricata sp. nov. 100, P. (F.) naja sp. nov. 101, P. (F.) sapitanduva sp. nov. 102, P. (F.) vulgaris sp. nov. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437269/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Figs 99, 100</figureCitation>
) approximately oval, not flattened dorsoventrally; small, between 6.2 to 8.0mm. Head (
<figureCitation box="[225,299,1581,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[190,1379,203,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1379,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 15. P. (F.) bahiensis sp. nov., holotype male. 4, head and thorax, dorsal view. 5, head, frontal view. 6, head and thorax, lateral view. 7, forewing. 8 – 15, male terminalia: 8, sternite VIII, ventral view. 9, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 10, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 11, subgenital plate, ventral view. 12, style and connective, dorsal view. 13, style, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, lateral view. 15, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 4 – 6 = 1.0 mm, 7 = 2.0 mm, 8 – 9 = 0.5 mm, 9 – 14 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437258/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Figs 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[311,341,1581,1606]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 27" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[184,1373,203,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1373,193,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 27. P. (F.) grossii sp. nov., holotype male. 16, head and thorax, dorsal view. 17, head, frontal view. 18, head and thorax, lateral view. 19, forewing. 20 – 27, male terminalia: 20, sternite VIII, ventral view. 21, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 22, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 23, subgenital plate, ventral view. 24, style and connective, dorsal view. 25, style, lateral view. 26, aedeagus, lateral view. 27, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 16 – 18 = 1.0 mm, 19 = 2.0 mm, 20 – 2 1 = 0.5 mm, 22 – 27 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437259/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">16</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, not produced; median length of crown approximately half as long as interocular width; crown with transverse parallel striae; anterior margin of crown approximately parallel to posterior margin; transocular width of head slightly narrower than maximum pronotum width. Ocelli equidistant between eyes and median line and near anterior margin of crown. Head (
<figureCitation box="[791,881,1689,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1872,1895]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,194,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[203,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 43. P. (F.) intricata sp. nov., holotype male. 32, head and thorax, dorsal view. 33, head, frontal view. 34, head and thorax, lateral view. 35, forewing. 36 – 43, male terminalia: 36, sternite VIII, ventral view. 37, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 38, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 39, subgenital plate, ventral view. 40, style and connective, dorsal view. 41, style, lateral view. 42, aedeagus, lateral view. 43, aedeagus dorsal view. Scale bars: 32 – 34 = 1.0 mm, 35 = 2.0 mm, 36 – 37 = 0.5 mm, 38 – 43 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437261/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Figs 34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[896,927,1689,1714]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 71" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1848,1871]" captionTargetBox="[228,1363,201,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[223,1363,193,1828]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 71. P. (F.) sapitanduva sp. nov., holotype male. 60, head and thorax, dorsal view. 61, head, frontal view. 62, head and thorax, lateral view. 63, forewing. 64 – 71, male terminalia: 64, sternite VIII, ventral view. 65, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 66, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 67, subgenital plate, ventral view. 68, style and connective, dorsal view. 69, style, lateral view. 70, aedeagus, lateral view. 71, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 60 – 62 = 1.0 mm, 63 = 2.0 mm, 64 – 65 = 0.5 mm, 66 – 71 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437264/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">62</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with crown-face transition rounded and with several parallel striae. Pronotum in lateral view, slightly declivous, with transverse striae on disc and posterior third. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[493,579,1761,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1872,1895]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,194,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[203,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 43. P. (F.) intricata sp. nov., holotype male. 32, head and thorax, dorsal view. 33, head, frontal view. 34, head and thorax, lateral view. 35, forewing. 36 – 43, male terminalia: 36, sternite VIII, ventral view. 37, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 38, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 39, subgenital plate, ventral view. 40, style and connective, dorsal view. 41, style, lateral view. 42, aedeagus, lateral view. 43, aedeagus dorsal view. Scale bars: 32 – 34 = 1.0 mm, 35 = 2.0 mm, 36 – 37 = 0.5 mm, 38 – 43 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437261/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Figs 35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[591,620,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 55" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[212,1368,200,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[204,1368,193,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 55. P. (F.) naja sp. nov., holotype male. 44, head and thorax, dorsal view. 45, head, frontal view. 46, head and thorax, lateral view. 47, forewing. 48 – 55, male terminalia: 48, sternite VIII, ventral view. 49, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 50, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 51, subgenital plate, ventral view. 52, style and connective, dorsal view. 53, style, lateral view. 54, aedeagus, lateral view. 55, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 44 – 46 = 1.0 mm, 47 = 2.0 mm, 48 – 4 9 = 0.5 mm, 50 – 55 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437262/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">47</figureCitation>
) without extra crossveins; appendix developed. Foreleg with AV and PV rows formed by few and sparse setae, AV row restricted to proximal half and PV with one to three setae, IC row formed by slightly arched comb of fine setae beginning at distal half of femur and extending to AM1. Hind leg with femoral setal formula 2:2:1; tibiae AD row with intercalary microsetae between macrosetae; first tarsomere with two rows of setae on plantar surface, medial row with setae slightly smaller than external row; apex with four or five patellae; second tarsomere with two rows of setae on plantar surface; apex with two apical patellae. Male sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[306,394,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 43" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1872,1895]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,194,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[203,1368,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 43. P. (F.) intricata sp. nov., holotype male. 32, head and thorax, dorsal view. 33, head, frontal view. 34, head and thorax, lateral view. 35, forewing. 36 – 43, male terminalia: 36, sternite VIII, ventral view. 37, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 38, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 39, subgenital plate, ventral view. 40, style and connective, dorsal view. 41, style, lateral view. 42, aedeagus, lateral view. 43, aedeagus dorsal view. Scale bars: 32 – 34 = 1.0 mm, 35 = 2.0 mm, 36 – 37 = 0.5 mm, 38 – 43 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437261/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Figs 36</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[407,436,1978,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 55" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[212,1368,200,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[204,1368,193,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 55. P. (F.) naja sp. nov., holotype male. 44, head and thorax, dorsal view. 45, head, frontal view. 46, head and thorax, lateral view. 47, forewing. 48 – 55, male terminalia: 48, sternite VIII, ventral view. 49, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 50, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 51, subgenital plate, ventral view. 52, style and connective, dorsal view. 53, style, lateral view. 54, aedeagus, lateral view. 55, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 44 – 46 = 1.0 mm, 47 = 2.0 mm, 48 – 4 9 = 0.5 mm, 50 – 55 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437262/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">48</figureCitation>
) commonly wider than long, partially hiding subgenital plates. Male pygofer with (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 55" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1865,1888]" captionTargetBox="[212,1368,200,1833]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[204,1368,193,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 55. P. (F.) naja sp. nov., holotype male. 44, head and thorax, dorsal view. 45, head, frontal view. 46, head and thorax, lateral view. 47, forewing. 48 – 55, male terminalia: 48, sternite VIII, ventral view. 49, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 50, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 51, subgenital plate, ventral view. 52, style and connective, dorsal view. 53, style, lateral view. 54, aedeagus, lateral view. 55, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 44 – 46 = 1.0 mm, 47 = 2.0 mm, 48 – 4 9 = 0.5 mm, 50 – 55 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437262/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">Figs 49</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[197,226,2013,2038]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 71" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1848,1871]" captionTargetBox="[228,1363,201,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[223,1363,193,1828]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 71. P. (F.) sapitanduva sp. nov., holotype male. 60, head and thorax, dorsal view. 61, head, frontal view. 62, head and thorax, lateral view. 63, forewing. 64 – 71, male terminalia: 64, sternite VIII, ventral view. 65, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 66, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 67, subgenital plate, ventral view. 68, style and connective, dorsal view. 69, style, lateral view. 70, aedeagus, lateral view. 71, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 60 – 62 = 1.0 mm, 63 = 2.0 mm, 64 – 65 = 0.5 mm, 66 – 71 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437264/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="536">65</figureCitation>
) or without short processes, on dorsal margin, at base; with tuft of hairlike setae near ventral margin; macrosetae dispersed on posterodorsal quadrant; posterior margin with (
<figureCitation box="[960,1047,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[190,1379,203,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1379,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 15. P. (F.) bahiensis sp. nov., holotype male. 4, head and thorax, dorsal view. 5, head, frontal view. 6, head and thorax, lateral view. 7, forewing. 8 – 15, male terminalia: 8, sternite VIII, ventral view. 9, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 10, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 11, subgenital plate, ventral view. 12, style and connective, dorsal view. 13, style, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, lateral view. 15, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 4 – 6 = 1.0 mm, 7 = 2.0 mm, 8 – 9 = 0.5 mm, 9 – 14 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437258/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">Figs 10</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1059,1088,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 71" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1848,1871]" captionTargetBox="[228,1363,201,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[223,1363,193,1828]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 71. P. (F.) sapitanduva sp. nov., holotype male. 60, head and thorax, dorsal view. 61, head, frontal view. 62, head and thorax, lateral view. 63, forewing. 64 – 71, male terminalia: 64, sternite VIII, ventral view. 65, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 66, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 67, subgenital plate, ventral view. 68, style and connective, dorsal view. 69, style, lateral view. 70, aedeagus, lateral view. 71, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 60 – 62 = 1.0 mm, 63 = 2.0 mm, 64 – 65 = 0.5 mm, 66 – 71 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437264/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">66</figureCitation>
) or without (
<figureCitation box="[1235,1317,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 27" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[184,1373,203,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1373,193,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 27. P. (F.) grossii sp. nov., holotype male. 16, head and thorax, dorsal view. 17, head, frontal view. 18, head and thorax, lateral view. 19, forewing. 20 – 27, male terminalia: 20, sternite VIII, ventral view. 21, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 22, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 23, subgenital plate, ventral view. 24, style and connective, dorsal view. 25, style, lateral view. 26, aedeagus, lateral view. 27, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 16 – 18 = 1.0 mm, 19 = 2.0 mm, 20 – 2 1 = 0.5 mm, 22 – 27 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437259/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) short and rounded protrusion near apex of pygofer. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[816,902,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[190,1379,203,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1379,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 15. P. (F.) bahiensis sp. nov., holotype male. 4, head and thorax, dorsal view. 5, head, frontal view. 6, head and thorax, lateral view. 7, forewing. 8 – 15, male terminalia: 8, sternite VIII, ventral view. 9, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 10, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 11, subgenital plate, ventral view. 12, style and connective, dorsal view. 13, style, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, lateral view. 15, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 4 – 6 = 1.0 mm, 7 = 2.0 mm, 8 – 9 = 0.5 mm, 9 – 14 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437258/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">Figs 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[915,944,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 27" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[184,1373,203,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1373,193,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 27. P. (F.) grossii sp. nov., holotype male. 16, head and thorax, dorsal view. 17, head, frontal view. 18, head and thorax, lateral view. 19, forewing. 20 – 27, male terminalia: 20, sternite VIII, ventral view. 21, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 22, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 23, subgenital plate, ventral view. 24, style and connective, dorsal view. 25, style, lateral view. 26, aedeagus, lateral view. 27, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 16 – 18 = 1.0 mm, 19 = 2.0 mm, 20 – 2 1 = 0.5 mm, 22 – 27 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437259/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">23</figureCitation>
) with hairlike setae on external margin; not produced posterad as far as apex of pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[672,747,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[190,1379,203,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1379,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 15. P. (F.) bahiensis sp. nov., holotype male. 4, head and thorax, dorsal view. 5, head, frontal view. 6, head and thorax, lateral view. 7, forewing. 8 – 15, male terminalia: 8, sternite VIII, ventral view. 9, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 10, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 11, subgenital plate, ventral view. 12, style and connective, dorsal view. 13, style, lateral view. 14, aedeagus, lateral view. 15, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 4 – 6 = 1.0 mm, 7 = 2.0 mm, 8 – 9 = 0.5 mm, 9 – 14 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437258/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">Figs 9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[761,792,224,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 27" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1882,1905]" captionTargetBox="[184,1373,203,1853]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1373,193,1858]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 27. P. (F.) grossii sp. nov., holotype male. 16, head and thorax, dorsal view. 17, head, frontal view. 18, head and thorax, lateral view. 19, forewing. 20 – 27, male terminalia: 20, sternite VIII, ventral view. 21, pygofer, valve and subgenital plate, lateral view. 22, apex of pygofer, ventral view. 23, subgenital plate, ventral view. 24, style and connective, dorsal view. 25, style, lateral view. 26, aedeagus, lateral view. 27, aedeagus posterior view. Scale bars: 16 – 18 = 1.0 mm, 19 = 2.0 mm, 20 – 2 1 = 0.5 mm, 22 – 27 = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/437259/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="537">21</figureCitation>
